Last week @felipenunesskate received his “signature” legs (for “chilling with friends without getting strange looks”) and then we surprised him with his signature skateboard model the next day. Thanks to @mcop_prosthetics @dupedupe & @davisonbob for helping to create all this magic. Felipe’s groundbreaking video will be out soon at @thrashermag but his pro model is available now at @birdhouseskateboards. The more I get to know him, the more impressed I am with his approach to life and unbreakable determination. No excuses!
🎶: @mrcamcole - “Albion”

node.text:
I got a request from PRK to be a guest singer in their online series, as they inch closer to playing live shows again. Most of their default song selections had been done by the time I was able to participate, but one song stood out: In The City. It was the first song I heard from The Jam, and has always been one of my favorites. Here’s my attempt to channel the prolific @paulwellerhq (who just released a new album!). The ending is my version of a mic/tail drop. Enjoy! 
Thanks @darrinpfeiffer @slee9383 @randybradbury @greghetson @alan_d9000 @900films for doing the heavy lifting on this one.

node.text:
After posting our 1999 doubles run last week, the feedback was incredible. I saw thousands of comments about remembering the event, and a genuine love for that era of skating. The nostalgia was so strong that we decided to do it again yesterday (22 years later). Some of the line was embellished - my 720’s are far less consistent than Andy’s these days - but we tried to match the tricks and the camera angles as best we could. And it just wouldn’t have been complete without the legendary @selema calling the action. Thanks for all of your support through these [many, many] years. We love you, and we still love skating as much as ever.
🎥: @cameronsanchez1 & @katnoaga 
Unrelated (but while you’re here): my NFT is finally dropping in 4/26 via @ethernitychain

Today I was “retiring” my Gymnast Plant for an upcoming project with @autograph.io when I stalled one longer than usual and started to fall in backwards… which gave me an idea. Introducing my first (and last) Gymnast to fakie. My perspiration should give you an idea of how long it took to finally commit. Scary stuff.
🎥: @cameronsanchez1

node.text: The irony here is that Sgt Pepper’s was the first album I ever bought. And I would have campaigned to include Hey Bulldog if I thought it was a possibility. “You know any more…?”

There is something cathartic about seeing @lizziearmanto doing a finger flip lein to tail in the exact same location where I dislocated my fingers last May, after she herself suffered a most horrific injury last October that could have ended her skating career. But we persevere and get back out there because it is the most fun, even when it hurts. 
🎥: @axelcrusher 📷: @mrzzz
